page.title: 01SOUTHREPPS
page.content:
Rural area consisting of mainly arable land slightly undulating, rising to approximately 200 feet above sea level at the cliffs at TRIMINGHAM. It includes the upper part of the sizeable (by Norfolk standards) village of SOUTHREPPS, and the outskirts TRIMINGHAM, and THORPE MARKET. Also included is the fairly sizeable private estate of TEMPLEWOOD.
An ever changing panorama of wonderful sunsets offset by the high skies. Prevailing winds give rise to stark and sometimes eerie shapes, as trees bend, and become tortured.
There are a number of listed buildings (some itemised in the text). Where new buildings have beeb erected, in the main an attempt has been made to evoke the traditional Norfolk style.
